'''Assistance publique – Hôpitaux de Paris (AP-HP)''' ({{IPA-fr|asistɑ̃s pyblik opito də paʁi}}) is the university hospital trust operating in Paris and its surroundings.

It is the largest hospital system in Europe and one of the largest in the world,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.paris-region.com/ard_uk/upload/document/D176.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-01-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070117112822/http://www.paris-region.com/ard_uk/upload/document/D176.pdf |archivedate=2007-01-17 |df= }}</ref> it provides health care, teaching, research, prevention, education and emergency medical service in 52 branches of medicine. It employs more than 90,000 people (including 15,800 physicians)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rapport-activite.aphp.fr/personnel.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-12-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720204058/http://rapport-activite.aphp.fr/personnel.php |archivedate=2011-07-20 |df= }}</ref> in 44 hospitals and receives more than 5,8 million annual patient visits.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rapport-activite.aphp.fr/activite_ambulatoire.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-04-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327062949/http://rapport-activite.aphp.fr/activite_ambulatoire.php |archivedate=2014-03-27 }}. This number covers consultations ("Activité ambulatoire externe") plus hospitalizations ("Activité médicale").</ref>

It is linked with the [[University of Paris]] and its seven colleges of medicine, two of odontology and two of pharmacy as AP-HP is the university hospital for the capital and its surroundings.

AP-HP is organized in several hospital local trusts, each associated to a faculty to offer integrative care to its population.

As a teaching hospital, AP-HP Trust is in charge of training healthcare professionals and doctors, and plays a prominent role in French healthcare research alongside [[Inserm]].

== History ==

Succeeding to the ''conseil général des hospices de Paris'', the ''Administration générale de l'Assistance publique'' was created by a law of January 10, 1849.
In 1961, the AP-HP became the public hospital system of Paris and its suburbs.

