{{For|the Monty Python sketch|Patient Abuse}} {{more footnotes|date=April 2013}} :''This article incorporates "medical abuse", which has a similar meaning but relates more specifically to harmful medical treatment rather than care in general, and may include victims who did not choose to be patients.''
'''Patient abuse''' or '''[[neglect]]''' is any action or failure to act which causes unreasonable suffering, misery or harm to the [[patient]].<ref name="sfc">{{cite web|title=Patient Abuse|url=https://www.stopfraudcolorado.gov/fraud-center/medicaid-fraud/patient-abuse|website=Stop Fraud Colorado|publisher=Colorado Attorney General's Office|accessdate=25 October 2017}}</ref> *'''Abuse''' includes [[physical abuse|physically striking]] or [[sexual assault|sexually assaulting]] a patient. It also includes the intentional withholding of necessary food, physical care, and medical attention. *'''Neglect''' includes the failure to properly attend to the needs and care of a patient, or the unintentional causing of injury to a patient, whether by act or omission.<ref>{{cite web|title=Medicaid Fraud Definitions|url=http://www.ag.idaho.gov/medicaidFraud/medicaidFraudDefinitions.html|website=Office of the Attorney General|publisher=State of Ohio|accessdate=25 October 2017}}</ref> Patient abuse and neglect may occur in settings such as hospitals,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Slavin|first1=Erik|title=Doctor faces court-martial in patient abuse case|url=https://www.stripes.com/news/doctor-faces-court-martial-in-patient-abuse-case-1.98060|accessdate=25 October 2017|agency=Stars & Stripes|date=16 January 2010}}</ref> nursing homes,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Larson|first1=Aaron|title=Warning Signs for Abuse and Neglect in Nursing Homes and Long-Term Care Facilities|url=https://www.expertlaw.com/library/medicine/minimal_guidelines.html|website=ExpertLaw|accessdate=25 October 2017|date=12 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Patient abuse - nurse struck off|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/wales/2989241.stm|accessdate=25 October 2017|agency=BBC News|date=30 April 2003}}</ref> clinics<ref>{{cite news|last1=Krell|first1=Alexis|title=Doctor charged with sex crimes at Bremerton clinic is at center of women’s lawsuit|url=http://www.thenewstribune.com/news/local/crime/article177478726.html|accessdate=25 October 2017|agency=The News Tribune|date=9 October 2017}}</ref> and during home-based care.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gorman|first1=Anna|title=When Home Caregivers Kill the Elderly With Neglect|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2015/01/when-home-caregivers-kill-the-elderly-with-neglect/384221/|accessdate=25 October 2017|publisher=The Atlantic|date=6 January 2015}}</ref>
