The '''Uganda AIDS Commission''' (UAC) is a national organization established by [[Parliament of Uganda|parliamentary statute]] in 1992. The Commission's main objective is to oversee the implementation of the national strategy to combat HIV/AIDS, adopted by the [[Government of Uganda]] in 1990.<ref>[http://www.iisd.org/50comm/commdb/desc/d26.htm About Uganda AIDS Commission]</ref>
==Leadership== The Commission is situated under the [[President of Uganda|Office of the President of Uganda]]. The current [[Chairman]] is '''Professor Vinand Nantulya'''. The [[Director General]] of the UAC is [[Christine Ondoa|Dr. Christine Joyce Ondoa]], a prominent consultant [[pediatrician]] and former [[Ministry of Health (Uganda)|Minister of Health]] (May 2011 - May 2013).<ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/201403050068.html Uganda: Christine Ondoa Starts Work At AIDS Commission]</ref>
